HENRY RICHMOND SLACK (HRS)















 HENRY RICHMOND SLACK (HRS)
 
 
 
 
 
Henry (Hank) Slack was until recently Chairman of Terra Industries (NYSE), an international nitrogen-based fertilizer company.  (After a lengthy takeover battle, Terra, a $5.5 bil company, was acquired by CF Industries at a premium of 235% to its unaffected price).   
 
 
 
HRS is a director of E. Oppenheimer and Son International Limited and on its Investment Committee.  He is the senior partner of Quarterwatch, LLC.  In addition, he is a director of several other non-listed companies mostly based in the United Kingdom.
 
 
 
HRS was born in Dayton, Ohio, on 1 February, 1950.  He attended secondary school in Switzerland and Groton School in Massachusetts.  He graduated from Princeton University in 1972 with a BA degree in history, and soon afterwards went to Johannesburg to join the Anglo American Corporation as a trainee in the finance division.
 
 
 
In 1974 he became personal assistant to then Deputy Chairman of Anglo American, and shortly after in 1975, he was appointed personal assistant to the Chairman, Harry Oppenheimer, a position HRS held in one form or another until Mr. Oppenheimer's retirement in 1982.  During this period, HRS became especially involved in the North American activities of the Anglo Group.  In 1981 he joined the board of Engelhard Minerals and Chemicals Corporation.  He was appointed to the board of Anglo American in 1983 and soon thereafter joined its Executive Committee.  Following this he was actively involved in the full range of the corporation’s mining, financial and industrial activities worldwide.
 
 
 
HRS joined the board of Minorco in 1981.  In 1988 he was appointed Executive Director of Minorco in charge of North America.  During this time he played a significant role in Minorco’s bid for Consolidated Gold Fields. In 1992 HRS was appointed Chief Executive of Minorco, following which he oversaw the culmination of Minorco's transformation from an investment holding company into one of the world's leading operating natural resources groups.  As Chief Executive and within the sectors of base metals, gold and aggregates, he oversaw the purchase of new mining operations, expansion programs for existing ones, and exploration programs of approximately $4 billion. 
 
 
 
 
 
From 1981 – 1987 HRS was a director of Salomon Brothers Inc. (NYSE), and more recently SABMiller plc.  During his twenty-eight years with Anglo American and Minorco, 
 
HRS was a board member of numerous subsidiaries and associated companies of the Group worldwide.  He remained on the board of Engelhard Corporation until the company was purchased by BASF in 2007.  HRS continues to have a close and working relationship with the Oppenheimer family.  He is a Director of the family firm and a member of its Investment Committee.  
 
 
 
From 1985 to 2000, HRS was a trustee of Groton School and inter alia in the 1980’s of the Urban Foundation and Redhill School in South Africa.  He is currently a member of the Advisory Council of the Willow School, and a trustee of the Upper Raritan Watershed Association in New Jersey.  HRS enjoys skiing, tennis, riding and fishing.
 
 
He is married to Sarah Lawrence Slack.  Together they have six children, two of whom are still under the age of 21.  HRS and his family reside in Peapack, New Jersey.
 
 
Contact Information: 
 
 
Henry (Hank) Slack
Quarterwatch LLC
P.O. Box 28
Peapack, New Jersey   07977
Office Tel:  908-719-8877
Office Fax:  9098-719-9808
E-mail:  hank.slack@quarterwatch.com














